article.headline: S. Dakota 93, IPFW 84
article.story: VERMILLION, S.D. -- Charlie Westbrook scored 35 points, including a perfect 14 of 14 at the free-throw line, to lift South Dakota past IPFW 93-84 on Thursday night. Louie Krogman also had a big night for South Dakota (10-17, 5-12 Summit League) with 20 points and six assists. Trevor Gruis grabbed eight rebounds. Frank Gaines scored 30 points and pulled down eight rebounds for IPFW (10-18, 4-13). Trey McCorkle scored 18 points for IPFW and Joe Edwards had 10. Jonny Marlin had five assists. South Dakota triumphed despite being outscored 42-30 in the paint and 21-10 off the bench. South Dakota had a 13-7 scoring advantage off turnovers.
